File: Former president Jacob Zuma will not attend the state capture inquiry as was expected. JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma will not attend the state capture inquiry as was expected. His lawyer, Eric Mabuza says Zuma is too busy preparing for his corruption trial. He says the Zondo Commission set the dates for Zuma's appearance without communicating with them. READ:Â Jacob Zuma pens letter challenging Ramaphosa The former president was expected to appear before the commission next week, after a postponement in January due to ill health. He made a series of allegations when he appeared at the inquiry in July last year.